AutomaticClient, BetrayalModelSupplier, HandicapEnterpriseAgent, StochasticAutomaticEnterpriseAgent, Supplier
public class AutomaticEnterpriseAgent
extends EnactmentEnterpriseAgent

This agent will automatically respond to contract events, according to several parameters that can be used to adjust its stochastic contractual behavior. This behavior does not distinguish among different types of obligations.

Method Detail

setup

protected void setup()
Description copied from class: EIAgent
This setup method:
  • iterates through the arguments provided to the agent to build the Properties object accordingly
  • registers the SL and Leap languages
  • registers the ei-management ontology
  • generates the public/private key pair for this agent
  • creates a responder behaviour for the EI_MANAGEMENT_ONTOLOGY
When extending this class, override this method to create agent behaviour(s) and invoke super.setup().

handleObligationReport

protected boolean handleObligationReport(Obligation obl)
Handles an obligation report. In this implementation, if this agent is the obligation's bearer, it will consider fulfilling according to the following optional arguments:
  • obligation_fulfillment_probability: a value in [0,1], default is 1.0
  • obligation_delayed_fulfillment_probability: a value in [0,1], default is 0.0
  • obligation_fulfillment_min_time: a value in [0,1+], default is 0.0
  • obligation_fulfillment_max_time: a value in [0,1+], default is 1.0

Specified by:
handleObligationReport in class EnactmentEnterpriseAgent
Parameters:
obl - The obligation report
Returns:
true if this agent is the obligation's bearer and chooses to fulfill the obligation; false otherwise

handleLivelineViolationReport

protected boolean handleLivelineViolationReport(LivelineViolation lviol)
Handles a liveline violation report. In this implementation, if this agent is the obligation's counterparty, it will consider denouncing according to the following optional arguments:

  • liveline_violations_denounce_min_time: a value in [0,1+], default is 0.0
